DAY 30 CIRCUIT BREAKER SERIES
CHATPATI ARBI
SPICY TANGY TARO (Gentlemans Toe 🙄 never understood why its called so or where the name came from)

I make Arbi this way because this is one vege that irritates my throat if not cooked well.
So I boil it in the pressure cooker, one whistle,  just enough to be peel it. Then cut it, deep fry it, and then cook it in jeera and onion tadka (temperting)
The spices used are coriander pwd, cumin pwd, chilli pwd, turmeric pwd and amchoor (dry mango pwd). A dash of lemon juice & chopped coriander leaves before serving. .

@vidhuram Ahhh I see. Thanks so much for the tip Vidhya 💕. Will sure try it next time. My mom used to cook it this way, because deepfrying it seemed to work for the irritation.
Add a small piece of tamarind when boiling Anu - it helps with taking away the irritation .
@a_sunbird_of_passage Anu, I make it without onion only when I am lazy to chop it 🤣🤣 But its equally yum without onion too

We make something similar too.. just no onions.. and rather roast them
